d). The 1-CPU limit may be\n  undersized for current workload. Under sustained load, master\n  election heartbeats could be delayed, risking false master failovers.\n  Not a security issue but a reliability/availability concern.\n\n====================================================================\nCLUSTER INVENTORY (as-found, unchanged)\n====================================================================\nNodes:             3 (es-cluster-0, es-cluster-1, es-cluster-2)\nRoles per node:    master, data, ingest (no role separation)\nES Version:        8.11.1 (Lucene 9.8.0)\nHeap per node:     512 MB (Xms=Xmx=512m)\nHeap usage:        es-cluster-0: 61%, es-cluster-1: 19%, es-cluster-2: 33%\nSwap:              disabled on all nodes (correct)\nIndices:           1 (audit-index: 3 primary / 1 replica / 0 documents)\nCluster UUID:      k37YY0uDR2KrBpXnKSjkiA\nCluster health:    GREEN\nServices:          es-http (ClusterIP 10.96.231.37:9200),\n                   es-cluster headless (:9300)\nKubernetes Secrets: NONE (consistent with auth being disabled)\nNetworkPolicies:   NONE\nPod securityContext: NONE configured\n\n====================================================================\nAUDIT METHODOLOGY - READ-ONLY, NO CHANGES MADE\n====================================================================\nAll data collected via read-only kubectl and unauthenticated curl.\nNo cluster settings, indices, pods, or resources were modified.\nAPIs queried (read-only GET):\n  /_cluster/settings?flat_settings=true\n  /_all/_settings\n  /_cluster/health\n  /_nodes (settings + stats for indices, os, jvm, process)\n  /_cat/indices\n  /_cat/nodes\nkubectl commands: get pods, statefulset, svc, secret, networkpolicy,\n  configmap, and describe/jsonpath on StatefulSet spec.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null,"userModified":false}}
